def population_calculation(timestamp):
    yearly_population = {"2020":21710000,"2021":22390000,"2022":23070000,"2023":23770000,"2024":24480000,"2025":25000000}
    proportion_target_population = 0.04
    to_return = yearly_population[str(timestamp.year)] * proportion_target_population * 1/12
    return to_return

def zero_dose_debt(serie_vac, serie_pop):
    to_return = []
    if len(serie_vac) == len(serie_pop):
        for i in range(len(serie_vac)):
            to_return.append(max(serie_pop.iloc[i] - serie_vac.iloc[i],0))
    return to_return

corrected_dataElement = 'GaneshAID_penta1_cov'

df_mali_corrected = df_mali_dict['uNwqkUQ7Qp1'].copy()
df_mali_corrected['population'] = df_mali_corrected.index.map(lambda x: population_calculation(x))
df_mali_corrected['dataElement'] = corrected_dataElement
df_mali_corrected['name'] = 'Estimation Couverture Penta1'
df_mali_corrected['source'] = 'GaneshAID'
df_mali_corrected['value'] = df_mali_corrected['value'] / (df_mali_corrected['population'] + zero_dose_debt(df_mali_corrected['value'].shift(-1), df_mali_corrected['population'].shift(-1))) * 100

label_dict[corrected_dataElement] = {'name':'penta1_coverage','label':'Estimate Penta1 Coverage by GaneshAID'}
df_mali_dict[corrected_dataElement] = df_mali_corrected

df_mali_dict[corrected_dataElement].head(10)

# Plot daily and weekly resampled time series together
fig, ax = plt.subplots(len(df_mali_dict),1, figsize=(14, 16))
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace = 0.8)

for i in range(len(df_mali_dict)):
    label = list(label_dict.values())[i]['label']
    data = list(df_mali_dict.values())[i]

    ax[i].plot(data['value'],
            marker='.', linestyle='-', linewidth=0.5, label='Monthly')

    data_year_mean = data['value'].resample('YE').mean()
    data_year_mean.index = data_year_mean.index.map(lambda x: x + pd.offsets.DateOffset(months=-6))
    data_year_mean.index = data_year_mean.index.map(lambda x: x + pd.offsets.DateOffset(days=-29))
    ax[i].plot(data_year_mean,
            marker='o', markersize=12, linestyle='-', label='Yearly Mean Resample')

    data_rm = data['value'].rolling(3, center=True).mean()
    ax[i].plot(data_rm,
            marker='o', markersize=6, linestyle='-', label='3 months rolling mean')
    ax[i].set_ylabel('{} (DHIS2)'.format(label))
    ax[i].legend()

from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
import warnings

# Test stationarity
# ==============================================================================
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

data_diff_1 = data_train.diff().dropna()
data_diff_2 = data_diff_1.diff().dropna()

print('Test stationarity for original series')
print('-------------------------------------')
adfuller_result = adfuller(data)
kpss_result = kpss(data_train)
print(f'ADF Statistic: {adfuller_result[0]}, p-value: {adfuller_result[1]}')
print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]}, p-value: {kpss_result[1]}')

print('\nTest stationarity for differenced series (order=1)')
print('--------------------------------------------------')
adfuller_result = adfuller(data_diff_1)
kpss_result = kpss(data_train.diff().dropna())
print(f'ADF Statistic: {adfuller_result[0]}, p-value: {adfuller_result[1]}')
print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]}, p-value: {kpss_result[1]}')

print('\nTest stationarity for differenced series (order=2)')
print('--------------------------------------------------')
adfuller_result = adfuller(data_diff_2)
kpss_result = kpss(data_train.diff().diff().dropna())
print(f'ADF Statistic: {adfuller_result[0]}, p-value: {adfuller_result[1]}')
print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]}, p-value: {kpss_result[1]}')
